title: Danny Says
description: This documentary profiles eccentric publicist Danny Fields, who helped launch the careers of innovative new artists who would become musical icons.
actors: Danny Fields, Iggy Pop, Alice Cooper, Judy Collins

title: Daughters of Destiny
description: Five girls from India's most impoverished families attend a boarding school designed to create opportunities as they strive for a brighter future.

title: David Blaine: Real or Magic?
description: Daredevil illusionist David Blaine visits Harrison Ford and other celebrities in their homes and performs feats of mind-bendingly impossible magic.

title: David Blaine: Street Magic
description: Renowned magician David Blaine performs illusions and tricks up close in street performances that awe and amaze his in-person, on-the-ground audience.

title: David Blaine: What Is Magic?
description: David Blaine travels the country wowing audiences with mind-bending magic tricks, from making cards vanish to catching a speeding bullet in his mouth.

title: De Palma
description: Iconoclastic film director Brian DePalma takes a look back at the production of such classic movies as "Carrie," "Scarface" and "The Untouchables."

title: Death Row Dogs
description: Delve into issues surrounding dangerous dogs, including attacks on humans, criminals who run fighting rings and police efforts to curb problems.

title: Decanted.
description: This lyrical documentary spotlights the vineyard-rich region of Napa Valley, California, and the winemakers who call it home.

title: Decoding Desire
description: Scientists explore the sexual behavior of animals like rats and peacocks before looking at how desire works in male and female humans.

title: Defying the Nazis: The Sharps' War
description: This film documents the story of minister Waitstill Sharp and his wife, Martha, who risked everything to save thousands of refugees fleeing the Nazis.

title: Diana: 7 Days That Shook the World
description: This illuminating documentary examines the aftermath of Princess Diana’s tragic death and the tense, dramatic week leading up to her funeral.

title: Discovering Bigfoot
description: Follow Todd Standing, Dr. Jeff Meldrum and other researchers into the wilderness, where they try to capture definitive proof of Sasquatch's existence.

title: Disturbing the Peace
description: This documentary follows former Palestinian and Israeli soldiers, tired of endless war, who form a group advocating peace through nonviolent action.

title: Dogs
description: These six intimate stories explore the abiding emotional bonds that form between dogs and their caregivers, no matter the circumstances.

title: Down The Fence
description: The human-equine bond propels the unique and challenging sport of reined cow horse, in which dedicated trainers compete for the national championship.

title: Dream Big: Engineering Our World
description: Narrated by Jeff Bridges, this compelling documentary examines some incredible achievements of engineering from across the globe.

title: Drunk Stoned Brilliant Dead: The Story of the National Lampoon
description: "National Lampoon" was born in the '70s to poke fun at the establishment and everything else. This documentary celebrates those who formed its legacy.

title: Dying to Know: Ram Dass & Timothy Leary
description: Icons of '60s counterculture, Harvard psychologists Timothy Leary and Ram Dass became estranged until an illness inspired their fascinating reunion.
